colubrisTextualConventions.name: colubrisTextualConventions
colubrisTextualConventions.contactinfo: Colubris Networks Postal: 200 West Street Ste 300 Waltham, Massachusetts 02451-1121 UNITED STATES Phone: +1 781 684 0001 Fax: +1 781 684 0009 E-mail: cn-snmp@colubris.com
colubrisTextualConventions.description: This module defines the Textual Conventions used in Colubris Networks enterprise MIBs.

ColubrisAuthenticationMode.name: ColubrisAuthenticationMode
ColubrisAuthenticationMode.description: Specifies the authentication mode to be used. local: The authentication is done locally from the device's local database information. profile: An authentication profile is used in order to retrieve the authentication parameters. localAndProfile: The authentication is done locally first. If it fails an authentication profile is used.

ColubrisUsersAuthenticationMode.name: ColubrisUsersAuthenticationMode
ColubrisUsersAuthenticationMode.description: Specifies the authentication mode to be used. none: Users are not allowed to login. local: User authentication is done via the local user accounts. profile: A third-party authentication server is used. localAndProfile: Authentication is done locally first. If it fails, a third-party authentication server is used.

ColubrisUsersAuthenticationType.name: ColubrisUsersAuthenticationType
ColubrisUsersAuthenticationType.description: Specifies the authentication type to be used. mac: Users are authenticated using their MAC addresses. ieee802dot1x: Users authenticated through 802.1X. html: Users authenticated via the HTML login page.

ColubrisNotificationEnable.name: ColubrisNotificationEnable
ColubrisNotificationEnable.description: Specifies the generation of notification traps. enable: Enables the generation of the associated notification. disable: Disables the generation of the associated notification

ColubrisProfileIndex.name: ColubrisProfileIndex
ColubrisProfileIndex.description: A profile index refers to an entry in the RADIUS server profile table.

ColubrisProfileIndexOrZero.name: ColubrisProfileIndexOrZero
ColubrisProfileIndexOrZero.description: A profile index refers to an entry in the RADIUS server profile table. When the special value Zero is specified, no RADIUS server profile is selected.

ColubrisServerIndex.name: ColubrisServerIndex
ColubrisServerIndex.description: A server index refers to an entry in the RADIUS server table.

ColubrisServerIndexOrZero.name: ColubrisServerIndexOrZero
ColubrisServerIndexOrZero.description: A server index refers to an entry in the RADIUS server table. When the special value Zero is specified, no RADIUS server is selected.

ColubrisSSID.name: ColubrisSSID
ColubrisSSID.description: A generic service set identifier (SSID) convention is defined here and used throughout the Colubris proprietary MIBs. This specific textual convention is used for inputing SSIDs.

ColubrisSSIDOrNone.name: ColubrisSSIDOrNone
ColubrisSSIDOrNone.description: A generic service set identifier (SSID) convention is defined here and used throughout the Colubris proprietary MIBs. This specific textual convention is used when displaying SSIDs.

ColubrisSecurity.name: ColubrisSecurity
ColubrisSecurity.description: An enumeration of the different Security modes allowed in the Colubris products. NOTE: 'unknown'- Could not identify the protection mode. 'none' - No wireless protection. 'wep' - WEP (static keys). 'ieee802dot1x' - 802.1X no encryption. 'ieee802dot1xWithWep' - 802.1x + WEP (dynamic keys). 'wpa' - 802.1X + TKIP + Key source AAA profile. 'wpaPsk' - 802.1X + TKIP + Key Source Pre-Shared Key.

ColubrisPriorityQueue.name: ColubrisPriorityQueue
ColubrisPriorityQueue.description: An enumeration of the different queues supported in the QOS and Bandwidth control feature.

ColubrisDataRate.name: ColubrisDataRate
ColubrisDataRate.description: An enumeration of the different data rates supported on a per VSC basis.

ColubrisRadioType.name: ColubrisRadioType
ColubrisRadioType.description: An enumeration of the different supported radio types.
